RCA framework
=============

0) Requirements

You need to have Java > 1.5.0 installed on your system.

1) Installation

Just unzip the erca.zip archive.

2) Usage

The main command is:

java -jar erca.jar

Arguments for this command are:

clfdot src tgt
	description: generate a dot file in tgt corresponding to the given (src) concept lattice family
	example: clfdot test.clf.xmi test.clf.dot
	
clfbuild --rcft src xmi tgt
	description: generate the XMI (xmi) and the concept lattice family (tgt) corresponding to the given relational context family (src) in the rcft format
	example: clfbuild --rcft test.rcft test.rcf.xmi test.clf.xmi
	
clfbuild --xmi src tgt
	description: generate the concept lattice family (tgt) corresponding to the given relational context family (src) in the xmi format
	example: clfbuild --xmi test.rcf.xmi test.clf.xmi
	
rcfhtml --rcft src tgt
	description: generate the HTML code in tgt corresponding to the given relational context family (src) in the rcft format
	example: rcfhtml --rcft test.rcft test.rcf.html
	
rcfhtml --xmi src tgt
	description: generate the HTML code in tgt corresponding to the given relational context family (src) in the xmi format
	example: rcfhtml --xmi test.rcf.xmi test.rcf.html 